Name: Europe Euro-19 Unemployment Rate
Metadata: This is an average of Unemployment Rates for the 15 members of the European Union prior to its expansion to 25 then 27 members. Source: Eurostat. Eurostat collects data from the statistical agencies of the 27 member countries of the European Economic Community, candidate countries (Macedonia, Croatia and Turkey), EFTA countries (Iceland, Norway, Liechtenstein and Switzerland) as well as other countries (Japan, Australia, United States). Statistical agencies within each country disseminate their national data to Eurostat in order that it can be made available in a consistent format.
